in their cars and gas stations?

01:16:40.363 --> 01:16:43.031
Besides, it's not the eagles
I worry about.

01:16:43.065 --> 01:16:46.034
It's the dry drought weather
that's killing these trees.

01:16:46.068 --> 01:16:48.638
There's not enough
rain and water.

01:16:48.672 --> 01:16:51.840
Even worse, the spruce bark
beetles are eating

01:16:51.875 --> 01:16:54.811
These trees
to death and turning them
from green to red.

01:16:54.843 --> 01:16:58.013
I remember when those
beetles used to die out
during the winter.

01:16:58.046 --> 01:17:01.016
But now with the dry climate
they've multiplied

01:17:01.049 --> 01:17:02.886
And taken over the forest.

01:17:02.918 --> 01:17:04.620
Take a look at that
dead redwood up there.

01:17:04.620 --> 01:17:07.190
That was killed
by a bark beetle.

01:17:13.129 --> 01:17:15.764
This damn global warming.

01:17:15.798 --> 01:17:18.702
It's the cause of dry climate
and bark beetles

01:17:18.734 --> 01:17:21.036
And death of the trees
and forest.

01:17:21.069 --> 01:17:23.105
I can protect these trees

01:17:23.139 --> 01:17:25.809
Against greedy
lumber companies

01:17:25.841 --> 01:17:28.812
And bad campers who start
forest wildfires.

01:17:28.844 --> 01:17:32.816
But it's impossible to protect
them against global warming.

01:17:32.848 --> 01:17:35.151
- What's your name?
- I'm tom hill.

01:17:35.184 --> 01:17:38.755
I'm rod. This is nathalie,
Susan and Tony.

01:17:41.758 --> 01:17:43.159
You can come with us.

01:17:43.192 --> 01:17:45.729
Oh, I can't.

01:17:45.762 --> 01:17:47.062
This is my home.

01:17:47.095 --> 01:17:50.132
I have to stay here
to protect these trees
from further harm.

01:17:50.166 --> 01:17:53.937
Enjoy and appreciate these
trees while you can.

01:17:56.840 --> 01:17:59.407
In a few years
they'll be gone.

